                           +--------------+
                           | Introduction |
                           +--------------+

Football Statistician Professional is a piece of software which allows
you to have a detailed analysis of a football league.  The program was
written for football results  and  is  aimed  to  be used for football
leagues.  You may, however use  it  for  other types of leagues.  This
easy to use program allows you to generate league tables with ease.


                             +----------+
                             | The Menu |
                             +----------+

The main menu of the  program  lists  a  variety  of options.  You may
refer to each of these options  by  skipping to the different sections
of this documentation.  The use of  the  main menu is simple.  Use the
mouse pointer to click at  the  option  of  your  choice, use the left
mouse button to make the selection.


        Section                 Option
        -------                 ------

        1                       Enter New Result
        2                       Delete Result
        3                       Deduct League Points
        4                       Compile League Table
        5                       View Statistics
        6                       View Graph
        7                       View Tables/Team Tables
        8                       View Results
        9                       Predict Result
        10                      Team Results Comparison
        11                      Load/Save Files
        12                      Configuration
        13                      Quit


                   +------------------------------+
                   | Section 1 : Enter New Result |
                   +------------------------------+

If you have not started a new league  you will be required to edit the
league details.  This  involves  filling  out  a  form  which comes up
automatically if the file contains no results.  If you wish to clear a
file you can do so by selecting the option from the main menu.

When starting a new file, you  must  enter  the  name of the league by
typing it in on the form.   Select  the  number  of times a team plays
each other in the league  by  using  the left/right arrow keys.  Enter
the names of the teams by  selecting  the  team and entering the name.
Use the up/down arrows to select the team of your choice.  Below is an
example of a completed form :

LEAGUE NAME : SENSIBLE SOCCER LEAGUE           <
TEAMS x 2

TEAM 1      : CRAIG
TEAM 2      : PHIL
TEAM 3      : PAUL
TEAM 4      : ROY

The arrow is the cursor use to select/edit the names.

Once a file is defined, at any time you enter a result which brings up
a page showing a table looking like this :

            +---------------+ +--+ +---------------+ +--+
            | CRAIG         | |0 | | CRAIG         | |0 |
            | PHIL          | |1 | | PHIL          | |1 |
            | PAUL          | |2 | | PAUL          | |2 |
            | ROY           | |3 | | ROY           | |3 |
            +---------------+ |4 | +---------------+ |4 |
                              |5 |                   |5 |
                              +--+                   +--+

              CRAIG            0     ROY              1

The goals will continue down in a  column  up until 24.  At the bottom
is the score.  The first team  is  the  home team, the home goals, the
away team and the away goals.  Simply select the teams in the relevant
columns and select the  score.   Use  the  left  mouse  button for the
selecting.  To enter the  result  press  the  right mouse button.  You
will then be shown the form again  ready to input the next result.  If
you have finished then press the right mouse button.

The result entering process is also exited by inputting a result where
the teams have already played on the requested number of times, or you
have tried to input a result where a team plays itself.

If the preference is on then  a  page  of  the results entered will be
shown.  This allows you to check if the results are correctly entered.


                    +---------------------------+
                    | Section 2 : Delete Result |
                    +---------------------------+

Use the icons along the bottom of the screen to select a page with the
result which you want to  delete  on.   Click  on  this result and the
computer will ask you to verify your choice as to delete the result or
not.  Click on your response  'yes'  or  'no'.   If you click on 'yes'
then the result will be deleted from the file.


                 +----------------------------------+
                 | Section 3 : Deduct League Points |
                 +----------------------------------+

If a team has had  points  deducted  for disciplinary reasons then you
are allowed to deduct the points.   Simply  select the team form which
points are to  be  deducted  and  enter  the  number  of  points to be
deducted from the team's points tally.


                 +----------------------------------+
                 | Section 4 : Compile League Table |
                 +----------------------------------+

There are three types of league table which can be compiled :

1. Full League Table
   This details statistics of home/away games

2. Existing League Table
   This details statistics of all games

3. Selected League Table
   This displays a table  from  any  match  number.  Simple select the
match number by clicking on the +/- boxes to change each numeric
   digit.  You also need to select the number of games played by each
   team by clicking on the +/- boxes.

The abbreviations are as follows :

W   - Won
D   - Drawn
L   - Lost
FOR - Goals For
AGA - Goals Against
GD  - Goal Difference (FOR - AGA)
PTS - Points

If colour coding is on then the  teams in the promotion and relegation
zones will be hi-lited.  The team which  has been selected as the team
to be followed may also be hi-lited.

You can view a team's last  results  by  clicking on the team from the
league table.  A window will display  the  last matches by the team in
question.  To exit the window press  the left mouse button.  Press the
right mouse button to exit the league table.


                   +-----------------------------+
                   | Section 5 : View Statistics |
                   +-----------------------------+

There are several types of statistic table which can be viewed :

1. General Statistics
   This details general league statistics.  The percentages are
   displayed in yellow on the right side of the page.

2. Team Statistics
   This details team statistics.  You must fist select the team
   which you wish to view statistics on.

3. Team Statistics Comparison
   This details team statistics on two teams.  You must firstly select
   the teams which you wish to compare.


                      +------------------------+
                      | Section 6 : View Graph |
                      +------------------------+

There are several types of graph which can be viewed :

1. Average Goals Graph
   This graph displays each teams average number of goals scored and
   conceded.  The first bar shows the goals scored, the second shows
   the goals conceded for each team in the league.

   y-axis = Goals scored/conceded ; x-axis = Team

2. Points Progress Graph
   Two teams are selected allowing you to compare the progress of
   their points from game 1.  You can analyse the peaks/troughs of a
   team's progress in the league.  A flat line indicates a poor run
   whereas a steep diagonal line indicates a good run.

   y-axis = Points ; x-axis = Game Number
   line 1 = Team 1 ; line 2 = Team 2

3. Wins/Draws/Defeats Graph
   An ordered graph showing either wins/draws/defeats for each team in
   the league can be shown.  Simply click on the responding icon to
   vary the graph type between the three.

   y-axis = Total wins/draws/defeats ; x-axis = Team

4. Goals Scored/Conceded Graph
   First select the team in question, a graph will then display the
   number of goals scored for each game.  By clicking on the icons you
   can show the goals scored/conceded or both at once.

   y-axis = Goals scored/concede ; x-axis = Game Number

If the graph font is turned on  (see preferences) then numbers will be
displayed on certain graphs to display quantities.


                     +-------------------------+
                     | Section 7 : View Tables |
                     +-------------------------+

There are a variety of  different  table  which can be displayed.  The
tables display the top scoring matches.   You  must select the type of
table which could be :

1. Biggest Home Wins
   Shows the biggest home wins in order.
2. Biggest Away Wins
   Shows the biggest away wins in order.
3. Biggest Wins
   Shows the biggest wins in order.
4. Biggest Score Draws
   Shows the biggest score draws in order
5. Frequent Scores Chart
   This chart displays the frequency of scores in the league so far.
   The table shows numbers across the top representing the away team
   and the numbers down the page shows the home team.  Simply match up
   the home row with the away column to indicate the number of times
   this result has occurred.  Clicking on the number allows you to
   view all the results with this score line.

Tables can also be displayed by team allowing the user to select :

1. Biggest Home Wins
2. Biggest Away Wins
3. Biggest Home Defeats
4. Biggest Away Defeats
5. Biggest Score Draws


                     +--------------------------+
                     | Section 8 : View Results |
                     +--------------------------+

There are various results table which can be viewed :

1. All Results
   All results from match number one to the latest match are
   displayed.  Use the icons below to select the first/last page and
   adjust the page number.

2. Team Results
   Selection can be made on the team, you can select whether to view
   home/away games and scorelines with wins/defeats/draws.  Clicking
   on the word either turns the option to view this type of result.
   If away games is turned on then no away games are shown, if wins
   are turned off then no wins are shown.  Once selected you can use
   the icons to show the results.  There are two match numbers, one
   shows the league's match number and the other shows the team's
   individual match number.

3. Team Results Table
   A table of results by a team can be shown, simply select the team
   and a table shows all the results against each team in the league.

Clicking on a result opens a window  which displays a quick summary of
statistics for both teams.


                    +----------------------------+
                    | Section 9 : Predict Result |
                    +----------------------------+

The ability to predict  a  result  depending  on  current  form can be
predicted from this  option.   Simply  select  the  home/away teams in
question and a prediction will be displayed based on current home/away
form.


              +---------------------------------------+
              | Section 10 : Team Results Comparison |
              +---------------------------------------+

A breakdown of results is  displayed.   Either  all home results, away
results or both can be displayed  for  every  team in the league.  The
results are represented by a single character :

                   W - Win ; D - Draw ; L - Defeat

Using the icons below allows you to  adjust the mode either to display
home, away or all results.  Colour coding separates the type of result
in a different colour (this is enabled from preferences).


                   +-----------------------------+
                   | Section 11 : Loading/Saving |
                   +-----------------------------+

You have the option to  select  one  of  four  folders.  Use the right
mouse button to  flick  between  folders.   Each  folder  contains ten
files.  Clicking on a file allows  selection of this file, clicking on
'OK' executes the procedure to either  load/save.  The table shows the
statistics on the  file  including  the  date  (this  is adjusted from
preferences if you don't have an internal clock).  If you wish to edit
the name of the  file  then  you  can  do  so  by  clicking on the box
containing the league name.

External operations can  be  performed  allowing  you to import/export
files from other sources.  Simply specify the path and file name using
the AmigaDOS standards.


                    +----------------------------+
                    | Section 12 : Configuration |
                    +----------------------------+

The configuration of  the  program  is  altered.   You  can change the
league name along with  the  team  names.   Other  options include the
ability to select the league table relegation/promotion zones.  A zone
partition separates teams with a  set  number  of  points apart in the
league table.  You can hi-lite the default team by selecting on/off.

Auto loading of the first file  from  the  first folder is done if the
auto load option is on.   The  file  save  maximum lists the number of
results which are to be saved.  A graph font can be turned on/off.

The team followed can  be  selected  along  with  the number of points
awarded for a win.  The option  to  verify matches when entered can be
turned on/off  along  with  the  selection  of  the  last  1-5 matches
displayed from the league table.


                        +-------------------+
                        | Section 13 : Quit |
                        +-------------------+

The option to quit  the  package  returns  the  computer  to the state
before the program was loaded.  Since  the package is loaded from DOS,
You should be returned to DOS.


                           +--------------+
                           | Installation |
                           +--------------+

The package can be installed onto  another  disk or hard disk.  Simply
copy all the relevant files :

              FootStats-Folder-1 Directory and all files
              FootStats-Folder-2 Directory and all files
              FootStats-Folder-3 Directory and all files
              FootStats-Folder-4 Directory and all files
              Football-Stat-Pro file

From the start up sequence  assign  the directory which contains these
files to the  name  'Football-Statistician-Pro'.   For  example if the
directory containing these files is  called  'Football' then you would
enter the following from the CLI/Startup-sequence :

             Assign Football-Statistician-Pro: Football/


